---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro'

const codes = [
    {
        code: 400,
        label: 'Bad Request',
        when: 'Validation failed: missing form fields, malformed JSON, file too large, or content-type that does not match the file bytes.'
    },
    {
        code: 401,
        label: 'Unauthorized',
        when: 'No <code>Authorization</code> header, malformed token, unknown token, revoked token, or expired token. The response carries a <code>WWW-Authenticate: Bearer</code> header.'
    },
    {
        code: 402,
        label: 'Payment Required',
        when: 'Plan quota exhausted (e.g. 10 extractions / 30 days on the Free plan). Body includes <code>usage</code> and <code>product</code> so you can show the right upgrade prompt.'
    },
    {
        code: 404,
        label: 'Not Found',
        when: "The resource doesn't exist <em>or</em> belongs to a different account. We don't distinguish to avoid leaking existence to other users."
    },
    {
        code: 429,
        label: 'Too Many Requests',
        when: 'Rate limit hit. Response carries a <code>Retry-After</code> header (in seconds).'
    },
    {
        code: 500,
        label: 'Server Error',
        when: 'Something on our side broke. Safe to retry after a short backoff; persistent 500s should be reported.'
    }
]
---

<DocsLayout
    title="Errors & rate limits"
    section="resources"
    page="errors"
>
    <h1>Errors &amp; rate limits</h1>
    <p class="lede">
        Every error response shares the same shape. Every rate limit advertises
        itself in headers so your client can back off correctly.
    </p>

    <h2>Error envelope</h2>
    <p>
        Failures use the same <code>{`{ data, error, message }`}</code> envelope as
        successes — with <code>error: true</code> and a human-readable
        message:
    </p>

    <pre class="not-prose my-4 overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-4 text-[13px] text-gray-900"><code>{`{
  "data": null,
  "error": true,
  "message": "Invalid API token"
}`}</code></pre>

    <p>
        Some errors carry extra fields. Quota errors (402), for instance,
        include the user's current <code>usage</code> and the
        <code>product</code> that owns the limit:
    </p>

    <pre class="not-prose my-4 overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-4 text-[13px] text-gray-900"><code>{`{
  "data": null,
  "error": true,
  "message": "Extraction credit limit reached (10 per 30 days on the Free plan).",
  "usage": {
    "creditsUsed": 10,
    "creditsLimit": 10,
    "periodStart": "2025-04-01T00:00:00.000Z",
    "periodEnd": "2025-05-01T00:00:00.000Z",
    "percentUsed": 100,
    "remaining": 0
  },
  "product": { "slug": "free", "name": "Free" }
}`}</code></pre>

    <h2>Status codes</h2>
    <div class="not-prose my-4 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
        <table class="w-full text-left text-sm">
            <thead class="bg-gray-50 text-[11px] uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500">
                <tr>
                    <th class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">Code</th>
                    <th class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">Name</th>
                    <th class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">When you'll see it</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100 text-[13px] text-gray-700">
                {
                    codes.map((c) => (
                        <tr class="align-top">
                            <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-gray-900">{c.code}</td>
                            <td class="px-4 py-3 whitespace-nowrap">{c.label}</td>
                            <td class="px-4 py-3">
                                <Fragment set:html={c.when} />
                            </td>
                        </tr>
                    ))
                }
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </div>

    <h2>Rate limits</h2>
    <p>
        Limits are enforced per user (every API token belongs to a user, so
        all your tokens share the same buckets). When you exceed a limit the
        request returns <code>429</code> with a <code>Retry-After</code>
        header (seconds).
    </p>
    <div class="not-prose my-4 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
        <table class="w-full text-left text-sm">
            <thead class="bg-gray-50 text-[11px] uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500">
                <tr>
                    <th class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">Endpoint</th>
                    <th class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">Window</th>
                    <th class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">Cap</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100 text-[13px] text-gray-700">
                <tr>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-gray-900">POST /v1/extract</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3">60 seconds</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3">20 requests</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-gray-900">Auth (login flows)</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3">60 seconds</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3">10 requests / IP</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-gray-900">All other endpoints</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3">—</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3">no per-endpoint cap (yet)</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </div>

    <h2>Plan quotas (402)</h2>
    <p>
        Plan quotas are enforced separately from rate limits. A
        <code>POST /v1/extract</code> that passes the rate limiter still
        returns <code>402</code> if you've consumed your monthly extraction
        credits. The window is rolling 30 days — older runs age out and your
        balance recovers automatically. Upgrade plans at
        <a href="https://app.dvop.io/billing">/billing</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Recommended client behavior</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>
            Treat <code>5xx</code> and network errors as retryable; back off
            exponentially (e.g. 1s, 2s, 4s up to 30s) and give up after a few
            attempts.
        </li>
        <li>
            On <code>429</code>, honor <code>Retry-After</code>. Do not retry
            faster than the header says.
        </li>
        <li>
            On <code>401</code> with <code>"API token expired"</code> or
            <code>"API token revoked"</code>, do not retry — surface the
            error to the operator.
        </li>
        <li>
            On <code>402</code>, do not retry. The next call will fail too
            until usage drops below the limit or the user upgrades.
        </li>
    </ul>
</DocsLayout>
